Query Optimization: The process of tuning SQL statements and database configurations to reduce resource consumption and speed up execution times.

Index Management: Routinely rebuilding, reorganizing, or pruning database indexes to eliminate fragmentation and maintain peak search performance.

Execution Plans: Visual or textual roadmaps generated by the database engine showing the exact steps it will take to run a query.

Deadlock Analysis: Investigating events where two sessions block each other because both are waiting for resources held by the other, forcing the engine to kill one.

Blocking Sessions: Identifying and resolving scenarios where one active database connection holds a lock on a resource, forcing other connections to wait in line.
